  "name": "chi176_local_infra_bringup",
  "source": "service_bringup",
  "description": "Fresh local-dev bring-up of the V-Sekai infra for Linear CHI-176 (Finish V-Sekai project Part 1). Seven items (idtx_flow, crdb, baker, uro, zone_a, zone_b, obs) on a single workstation via launchd plists + native binaries (no Docker, no Kubernetes). The problem supplies: the item set, per-service descriptions, per-service dependency wrapper methods (complete_uro depends on complete_crdb and complete_baker, etc.), the win condition, and the top-level tasks. The domain (service_bringup) supplies only the abstract phase walk + verification primitives.",
  "linear": {
    "issue": "CHI-176",
    "url": "https://linear.app/chibifire/issue/CHI-176/finish-parts-of-the-v-sekai-project-or-it-will-haunt-me-part-1",
    "gitBranchName": "feature/chi-176-finish-parts-of-the-v-sekai-project-or-it-will-haunt-me-part",
    "priority": "Urgent",
    "blocks": ["CHI-180"],
    "blockedBy": ["CHI-221"]
  },
  "stack": {
    "idtx_flow": "OpenUSD Godot adapter (https://github.com/v-sekai-multiplayer-fabric/idtx-flow-v-sekai); imports .usda → .escn and exports .escn → .usda; build-time dependency baker links against. Tracked by CHI-254.",
    "uro": "Elixir/Phoenix; `mix phx.server` via launchd; uro-ZZZZ.chibifire.com; 2.0 GB",
    "crdb": "CockroachDB single-node via Homebrew (cockroachdb/tap/cockroach); reachable only by uro; crdb-WWWW.chibifire.com; 2.0 GB; certs under secrets/local/",
    "zone_a": "Native Godot headless from multiplayer-fabric-godot fork; binds UDP :4433 (no root needed for :443); zone-XXXX.chibifire.com; 2.0 GB",
    "zone_b": "Second zone server, identical to zone_a but distinct UDP port and plist label",
    "baker": "Native binary; watches local inbox/ directory; converts incoming USD via idtx_flow then writes to local casync-seed/; baker-AAAA.chibifire.com; 2.0 GB",
    "obs": "otelcol-contrib via Homebrew; OTLP receivers on default ports; obs-AAAA.chibifire.com; 2.0 GB"
  },
  "pass_conditions": {
    "idtx_flow_roundtrip_ok": "idtx-flow-v-sekai CI passes: a fixture .usda imports to .escn and exports back to .usda with no diff (CHI-254 acceptance)",
    "crdb_sql_ok": "`cockroach sql --certs-dir=secrets/local -e 'SELECT 1'` returns a row",
    "baker_inbox_ok": "drop a fixture .usda into inbox/, observe .scn seed written under casync-seed/ within 5 s",
    "uro_http_ok": "`curl -s http://localhost:4000/health` returns 200 and uro logs show CRDB connection accepted",
    "zone_a_udp_ok": "`nc -uvz 127.0.0.1 4433` reports open; WebTransport handshake completes",
    "zone_b_udp_ok": "second zone responds on its bound UDP port",
    "obs_otlp_ok": "OTLP HTTP receiver on 4318 accepts a synthetic span via curl"
  },
  "win_condition": "All seven items at phase=3, all seven stack_ready flags up, all seven pass_conditions met. Data-flow chain end-to-end verified: drop a .usda into baker's inbox → uro serves the converted bundle over HTTP → zone_a/zone_b instance it; crdb only reached via uro.",
  "dataflow": "idtx_flow (build-time, CHI-254) → baker (CHI-247, produces .scn seeds) → uro CDN (depends on crdb for metadata) → zone_a/zone_b (pull scenes from uro, CHI-248). obs is independent observability infra.",
